            <td><div class="repair-type">Motorized damper &amp; actuator</div><div class="repair-desc">Exhaust, supply, balance dampers</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$180&ndash;$640</div></td>
            <td>Damper actuator motor (common failure), end-switch contact failure, damper blade frame damage. Stuck-open dampers waste conditioned air; stuck-closed dampers can take the system out of code under fire-mode logic.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">Fusible links</div><div class="repair-desc">Heat-sensitive fire suppression actuators</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$20&ndash;$50 each</div><div class="price-parts-note">typically 4&ndash;12 per hood depending on suppression layout</div></td>
            <td>Annual replacement is NFPA 96 / UL-300 standard. Cheap parts &mdash; the labor (under-hood access, suppression-system pin cabling) is what you&rsquo;re paying for.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">Manual pull-station components</div><div class="repair-desc">Fire suppression manual actuator</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$80&ndash;$280</div></td>
            <td>Pull-handle replacement, breakable-glass front, mechanical linkage to suppression cabinet. Annual mechanical test as part of NFPA 96.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">Temperature probe &amp; sensors</div><div class="repair-desc">Hood-mount, duct-mount, demand-control optical</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$80&ndash;$320</div></td>
            <td>Probe degradation from grease exposure, calibration drift, sensor housing damage. More common on older platforms; modern sensors are more durable.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">Vapor-proof lighting</div><div class="repair-desc">Under-hood illumination &mdash; bulbs, ballasts, fixtures</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$40&ndash;$240</div></td>
            <td>Bulb burn-out (frequent on incandescent and halogen, less on LED retrofits), ballast failure on older fluorescent fixtures, lens gasket failure. LED retrofits on legacy fixtures pay back in lamp-replacement labor savings.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">Belt drive components</div><div class="repair-desc">Belt, pulley, sheave on belt-drive utility-set fans</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$40&ndash;$180</div></td>
            <td>Belt wear (annual replacement schedule on heavy-use rooftop fans), pulley misalignment, sheave wear. Cheap parts, frequent service item.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">End caps &amp; baffle frame</div><div class="repair-desc">Hood structural detail components</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$100&ndash;$420</div></td>
            <td>End-cap gasket replacement, baffle frame retention clip, hood-body seam sealant. Often surfaced during a cleaning visit when the rest of the hood is exposed.</td>
          </tr>
